headline: Alan G. Hassenfeld, former CEO of Hasbro and whose family founded the iconic toy maker, dies at 76
summary: NEW YORK — Alan G. Hassenfeld, a renowned philanthropist and former CEO of iconic toy company Hasbro Inc., the maker of G.I. Joe and Play-Doh, has died. He was 76, according to the toy company. ...
